javadoc: Listener methods that are called when changes to symbols are made.

methods.javadoc:
Notification that the given symbol has been added.
@param symbol the symbol that was added.
methods.name: symbolAdded
methods.comment: Notification that the given symbol has been added.

methods.name: symbolRemoved
methods.comment: Notification that a symbol was removed.

params.name: isLocal
params.comment:
true if the symbol was in the scope
 of a function

methods.name: symbolRenamed
methods.comment: Notification that the given symbol was renamed.

methods.javadoc:
Notification the the given symbol was set as the primary symbol.
@param symbol the symbol that is now primary.
methods.name: primarySymbolSet
methods.comment: Notification the the given symbol was set as the primary symbol.

params.name: symbol
params.comment: the symbol that is now primary.

methods.javadoc:
Notification that the scope on a symbol changed.
@param symbol the symbol whose scope has changed.
methods.name: symbolScopeChanged
methods.comment: Notification that the scope on a symbol changed.

params.name: symbol
params.comment: the symbol whose scope has changed.

methods.name: externalEntryPointAdded
methods.comment:
Notification that an external entry point was added at the
 given address.

params.name: addr
params.comment: the address that made an external entry point.

methods.name: externalEntryPointRemoved
methods.comment:
Notification that an external entry point was removed from the given
 address.

params.name: addr
params.comment: the address the removed as an external entry point.

methods.name: associationAdded
methods.comment:
Notification that the association between a reference and a 
 specific symbol has changed.

methods.name: associationRemoved
methods.comment:
Notification that the association between the given reference and
 any symbol was removed.

params.name: ref
params.comment: the reference that had a symbol association removed.

name: SymbolTableListener
comment: Listener methods that are called when changes to symbols are made.
